Very interesting Dr. Solco Walle Tromp (Dutch school biometeorologist that Dr. Ray Peat quotes often in articles) excerpt by my medical colleague here. 50% metabolism increase staying at the sea coast, but most people need 2-3 weeks to adapt to the climate to get the most benefit

Most people stay a week max at a sea resort and go back, but Russians here usually rent a house for the entire summer and stay for three months or so, I remember in a Russian textbook I read a month was the usual recommended time for a seacoast vacation with children. Thinking...

I MIGHT have seen a ball lightning as a kid btw. One night me and my mother were sitting in the living room and a round ball of fire just casually passed by our window. But it was in December in urban environment so small chance someone could have been testing weird fireworks (?)

Looked exactly like the one in the Wikipedia article picture but a bit larger and more fiery, like a very small sun, there was no thunderstorm or rain or anything noteworthy weatherwise as far as I remember.
I think it's a natural phenomenon
